1
00:00:04,288 --> 00:00:06,426
Welcome to English in a Minute.

2
00:00:07,405 --> 00:00:11,427
Some people use a large ball for exercise.

3
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:15,397
Is that what 'to get on the ball' means?

4
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:17,303
Hi, Anna.

5
00:00:17,589 --> 00:00:18,475
How has your day been?

6
00:00:18,588 --> 00:00:19,149
Great!

7
00:00:19,263 --> 00:00:19,890
Very great!

8
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:20,729
Very productive.

9
00:00:20,732 --> 00:00:23,530
I finished 3 reports and have only 1 more to do.

10
00:00:23,681 --> 00:00:24,203
Wow!

11
00:00:24,296 --> 00:00:26,020
You are on the ball!

12
00:00:26,488 --> 00:00:28,575
How did you do them so fast?

13
00:00:29,190 --> 00:00:29,712
Coffee.

14
00:00:30,066 --> 00:00:30,934
Lots of coffee.

15
00:00:30,957 --> 00:00:31,695
Do you want some?

16
00:00:31,695 --> 00:00:32,338
I'll get it.

17
00:00:32,365 --> 00:00:33,496
I'd love more coffee.

18
00:00:33,607 --> 00:00:34,290
Thank you.

19
00:00:34,301 --> 00:00:35,442
Uh, sure.

20
00:00:35,831 --> 00:00:38,899
But maybe not that much coffee.

21
00:00:40,983 --> 00:00:46,886
Someone who is on the ball finishes work quickly and ahead of time.

22
00:00:47,676 --> 00:00:54,697
We can also say a person should get on the ball when they need to work faster or better.

23
00:00:55,553 --> 00:00:57,840
And that's English in a Minute.
